data.event: The population was 1,166 at the 2010 census, up from the 2000 census, which counted 1,047 people.
Princeton was designated county seat in 1845.
In recognition of this Princeton hosts Calamity Jane Days Fall Festival each September.
Martha Jane Cannary (aka Calamity Jane) was born May 1, 1852 in Princeton, Missouri, the oldest of six children.
Parents Robert W. and Charlotte Cannary are listed in the 1860 census living nearby in Ravanna, Mercer County, Missouri.
The Cannary family moved to Montana in 1865, then on to Salt Lake City, UT where Robert Cannary died.
